OL,3,CBristol becomes England's least
OL,4,Caffordable city for rent
OL,6,FBristol has topped the charts as
OL,7,FEngland's most unaffordable city for
OL,8,Frent, with Bristolian renters paying
OL,9,Fnearly half their wages to landlords.
OL,11,FData from the Office for National
OL,12,FStatistics shows that renters in the
OL,13,Fcity spend an average of 45% of their
OL,14,Fincome on rent, the highest income/
OL,15,Frent percentage of any city in England
OL,16,Fand higher than the national average
OL,17,Fof 36%.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/3
